    <node id="Based on the meeting transcript, Cabinet Secretary Kirsty Williams does not seem to be opposed to having further conversations about the lessons learned from the Schools Challenge Cymru program if there is advice indicating that they have not sufficiently learned those lessons. However, she expresses confidence that they have already learned the lessons and are applying them to the wider school improvement agenda. She mentions that there has been ongoing dialogue with a variety of people involved in the program and that they are actively considering developing a Welsh toolkit around good practice, evidence base, and research. Therefore, while she is open to further conversations, her stance suggests that she believes that they have already effectively learned and applied the lessons from the Schools Challenge Cymru program." />
