ion, it ensures that schools identified as needing improvement will receive the required intensive support to help them make improvements. Examples of Schools Challenge Cymru schools have sustained progress even after the program has ended, indicating the potential for success with this new system.&#10;3. The Welsh Government is taking steps to improve the PDG (Pupil Development Grant) agenda at a regional level by appointing new regional PDG advisers. This will ensure individual school challenge advisers know what they should be looking for and doing, promoting good practice regionally. This further strengthens the support provided to schools in need of improvement under the new system.">
