he focus has historically been on free school meals due to their higher numbers.&#10;&#10;The lower number of looked-after children and the regionalization of PDG support contribute to less awareness about its availability for this group. It is essential to improve communication and understanding of PDG's role in supporting looked-after children, so that schools and consortia can effectively use these funds to narrow the attainment gap for this vulnerable group.">
