o those eligible for free school meals. This approach promotes more equitable distribution of resources and support across different vulnerable groups and helps narrow the attainment gap.&#10;3. Regional consortia's challenge and support advisers are crucial in fostering a regional approach to good practice, as they can facilitate collaboration and knowledge-sharing among schools to identify successful strategies for utilizing PDG funds effectively. This helps create a culture of continuous improvement and ensures that best practices are disseminated and adopted more widely.&#10;4. To maximize the impact of regional consortia's challenge and support advisers in this area, it is essential to provide them with adequate training, resources, and guidance on PDG policies and best practices. Strengthening their role and capacities will enable them to contribute more effectively to school improvement efforts and help ensure that PDG funds are used in ways that lead to better outcomes for disadvantaged learners.">
