ignificant minority of schools with recent appointments. This is one of the lessons learned from the three-year investment in school leadership.&#10;4. The Government is focusing on systems and processes, teacher quality, and collaborative activity in their wider school improvement program, the national mission, to address this issue.&#10;5. Expertise from the Schools Challenge Cymru program has been integrated into regional consortia to benefit all schools, not just a small proportion.&#10;6. The Government recognizes that there is always room for improvement and is strengthening the role of regional PDG (Pupil Deprivation Grant) advisers to ensure individual school challenge advisers know what they should be looking for and doing, with a regional approach to good practice.">
