    <edge source="1. The exact number of staff members that transitioned from Schools Challenge Cymru into the regional consortia was not provided in the transcript. However, Kirsty Williams mentioned that she met with some of them and many of the best personnel from Schools Challenge Cymru now work for the regional school improvement services.&#10;2. Kirsty Williams acknowledged Llyr Gruffydd's question about her commitment to applying lessons learned from Schools Challenge Cymru to the wider school improvement agenda, given that she didn't meet with a particular individual from the program until six or seven months after coming into post." target="1. The new schools categorization system in Wales provides a more targeted and intensive level of support for identified schools by using improvement boards to identify schools based on their level of need, with &quot;red&quot; schools entitled to 25 days of support. This is an increase from the 20 days of support provided under the Schools Challenge Cymru program. The new system targets resources towards schools with greater needs, regardless of their type or sector, which was not the case with the previous program that only supported secondary schools.&#10;2. This new system also addresses various challenges faced by children within the school setting, ensuring they receive the necessary support to remain in school. By incorporating well-being into the national mission, it ensures that schools identified as needing improvement will receive the required intensive support to help them make improvements. Examples of Schools Challenge Cymru schools have sustained progress even after the program has ended, indicating the potential for success with this new system.&#10;3. The Welsh Government is taking steps to improve the PDG (Pupil Development Grant) agenda at a regional level by appointing new regional PDG advisers. This will ensure individual school challenge advisers know what they should be looking for and doing, promoting good practice regionally. This further strengthens the support provided to schools in need of improvement under the new system.">
